      • checkNotNull

        static <T> T checkNotNull(T reference,
                          java.lang.String errorMessage)
                   throws org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException
        Ensures that an object reference passed as a parameter to the calling method is not null.
        Type Parameters:
        T - is the data type of the reference object.
        Parameters:
        reference - is the object, which should be checked.
        errorMessage - is the exception message to use if the check fails.
        Returns:
        the non-null reference that was validated
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException - is thrown in case the parameter is null.

      • checkEquality

        static <T> T checkEquality(T reference,
                           T comparisonObj,
                           java.lang.String errorMessage)
                    throws org.openbase.jul.exception.InvalidStateException
        Ensures that an object reference is equal to the object comparison. Furthermore, input parameters are checked to null.
        Type Parameters:
        T - is the data type of the reference and comparison object.
        Parameters:
        reference - is the object, which should be checked.
        comparisonObj - is the object, which should be equal to the reference.
        errorMessage - is the exception message to use if the check fails.
        Returns:
        the checked input reference that was compared.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.InvalidStateException - is thrown in case an input is null or the parameters are not equal.

      • checkNotNull

        static org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException.ExceptionStack checkNotNull(java.lang.Object reference,
                                                                             java.lang.String errorMessage,
                                                                             org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException.ExceptionStack exceptionStack)
        Ensures that an object reference passed as a parameter to the calling method is not null. Possible NotAvailableException is stacked and returned. Can be used to avoid large exception handling or rather describe as one-liner.
        Parameters:
        reference - is the object, which should be checked.
        errorMessage - is the exception message to use if the check fails.
        exceptionStack - is the exception stack to bundle possible exception. If null a new exceptionStack will be created.
        Returns:
        the exceptionStack with an following entry if the check fails. Otherwise input stack is returned.

      • checkNotNull

        static org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException.ExceptionStack checkNotNull(org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException.ExceptionStack exceptionStack,
                                                                             java.lang.Object... objects)
        Ensures that one or multiple object reference(s) passed as a parameter to the calling method is/are not null. Possible NotAvailableException is stacked and returned. By using one object reference use the single version method to be able to specify the content if exception is thrown.
        Parameters:
        exceptionStack - is the exception stack to bundle possible exception. If null a new exceptionStack will be created.
        objects - are the reference objects, which should be checked.
        Returns:
        the exceptionStack with an following entry if the check fails. Otherwise input exceptionStack is returned.
